  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law and national laws on money laundering intersect in several key ways:\n\n1. International Conventions and Treaties\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Mutual Legal Assistance\n- Countries cooperate in investigations\n- Sharing of financial intelligence\n- Cross-border asset seizure and recovery\n\n3. Standardization of Legal Frameworks\n- Common definitions of money laundering\n- Consistent reporting requirements\n- Minimum compliance standards\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- International sanctions\n- Blacklisting of non-compliant jurisdictions\n- Coordinated financial monitoring\n\n5. Information Sharing\n- Financial intelligence units (FIUs)\n- International banking networks\n- Real-time transaction tracking\n\n6. Regulatory Compliance\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) rules\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Due diligence requirements\n\n7. Technological Collaboration\n- Shared digital platforms\n- Advanced data analysis\n- Blockchain tracking mechanisms\n\nThese intersections create a complex, multilayered approach to combating money laundering globally, balancing national sovereignty with international cooperation.",
